Until the middle of the [[Nara period]] the Tajihi were one of the clans at the pinnacle of court society, but after this time became increasingly overshadowed by the [[Fujiwara clan]].{{sfnm|1a1=Mayuzumi|1y=1994}} Around the start of the [[:en:Heian period|Heian period]] the Tajihi clan mostly disappeared from the court society.{{sfnm|1a1=Mayuzumi|1y=1994}} The {{illm|Tantō clan|ja|丹党}}, a group of warriors in [[:en:Musashi Province|Musashi Province]] and one of the so-called {{illm|Musashi Shichitō|ja|武蔵七党}}, were remote descendants of the Tajihi clan who took up martial ways.{{sfnm|1a1=Mayuzumi|1y=1994}}
